&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
... -E -1 -c 7 ...  != ... -E -1 -c 6 ... &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Same offset error happened in &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/0a31c305-4848-4a9d-af77-d55745188fe2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/0a31c305-4848-4a9d-af77-d55745188fe2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="433619" author="adilger" created="Fri, 1 Nov 2024 16:37:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like this failure was an off-by-one in the stripe count of the last component:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;... -E -1 -c 7 ...  != ... -E -1 -c 6 ...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This &lt;em&gt;should&lt;/em&gt; have been handled by patch 55427, but I&apos;m not sure why it wasn&apos;t.  If a patch is made for this, it would be useful to print out the full file layouts in case of failure, so that it is possible to debug this further in the future.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="433115" author="yujian" created="Tue, 29 Oct 2024 05:01:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The failure only occurred once in all of the Lustre 2.16.0 RC test sessions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="433114" author="yujian" created="Tue, 29 Oct 2024 04:55:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Lustre 2.16.0 RC5 still failed: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/54b86e36-22e4-43f5-b38b-4633f7a3a94e&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/54b86e36-22e4-43f5-b38b-4633f7a3a94e&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
